  <h2>Banks aren't saying no to <em>you.</em><br>They're saying no to your category.</h2>
  <p>Banks have rigid underwriting boxes. If you're outside the box — too new, too thin a credit file, too much existing debt, wrong industry — they decline automatically. It's not personal. It's a scoring model that doesn't know your business, your jobs lined up, or your cash flow.</p>
  <p>Here's what most banks require that equipment lenders don't:</p>

