      <h3>2+ Years in Business</h3>
      <p style="margin:0">Banks rarely lend to businesses under 2 years old regardless of credit or cash flow. Equipment lenders look at the deal differently — the equipment itself is collateral.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reason-card">
      <div class="reason-label">Bank Requirement</div>
      <h3>680+ Credit Score</h3>
      <p style="margin:0">Most bank equipment loan programs require 680+ minimum. Equipment finance lenders specialize in programs starting at 550 — with rates that reflect the risk, not a hard no.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reason-card">
      <div class="reason-label">Bank Requirement</div>
      <h3>Tax Returns & Financials</h3>
      <p style="margin:0">Banks require 2 years of tax returns and business financials. Equipment lenders can approve deals under $75K with just an application and equipment invoice.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reason-card">
      <div class="reason-label">Bank Requirement</div>
